    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. So you're saying the \"stifling innovation\" argument is essentially just a smokescreen? To be fair, some economists argue that scale actually allows for the massive R&D spending that drives the industry forward. If you're looking at it from a purely utilitarian perspective, wouldn't a massive, efficient company be better for the economy than fragmenting it into smaller, less capable pieces?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
